ir immigration to the United States, where they became citizens. Now, through their complete biographies, we get to know them as individuals who lived through the most tempestuous and dangerous of times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aImmigrantszNew York (State)zNew YorkvBiography. 0aPolitical culturezRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistoryy20th century. 0aRussianszNew York (State)zNew YorkvBiography. 0aSecret servicezRussiaxHistoryy20th century. 4aArea Studies : European Studies. 4aArea Studies : Russian Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Memoir. 4aHistory : European History. 4aHistory : History. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848601740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438486017423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438486017/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles